s, summarize the topic, explain the methodology used, outline the thematic orientation, and link each chapter to other chapters in the book.Showcasing multimodal analysis in detail, this Reader is essential reading for undergraduate and postgraduate students, for emergent researchers, and for advanced scholars who wish to gain insight into the current state of multimodal research.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aCommunicationxMethodology. 0aModality (Linguistics) 0aModality (Linguistics). 0aOral communication. 0aSocial interaction. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aMultimodal Communication.  aMultimodal Discourse Analysis.  aMultimodal Interaction Analysis.  aSocial Semiotics.  aVisual Communication.1 aAbousnnouga, Gill, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAl Zydjaly, Najma, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBateman, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBezemer, Jeff, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDjonov, Emilia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEisenlauer, Volker, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFei, Victor Lim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGeenen, Jarret, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGibbons, Alison, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHiippala, Tuomo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIedema, Rick, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJewitt, Carey, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJones, Rodney H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary